dcterms:description: The CRASH dataset includes fMRI signals from 1940 scan sessions across 56 subjects, used for classifying brain signals into six tasks: resting state, visual working memory task, dynamic attention task, math task, dot-probe task, and psychomotor vigilance task.
dcterms:title: CRASH dataset

dcterms:description: The 200-ROI cortical parcellation is used to map voxel-level fMRI images into regional signals, facilitating the analysis of brain activity across different tasks.
dcterms:title: 200-ROI cortical parcellation

dcterms:description: fMRI data from various tasks including Rest, Visual Working Memory (VWM), Dynamic Attention (DYN), Dot-Probe (DOT), Math (MOD), and Psychomotor Vigilance Task (PVT) is utilized for analyzing brain dynamics.
dcterms:title: fMRI data from various tasks
